Date of Birth: July 31, 1920<br/>
Birthplace: Delta, Utah, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: October 1, 1978<br/>
Death: August 10, 2007<br/>
<br/>
Born July 31, 1920, in Delta, Millard Co., Utah, to George A. Faust and Amy Finlinson.
Sustained an Assistant to the Twelve Oct. 6, 1972, at age 52, and to the Presidency of the Seventy Oct. 1, 1976;
sustained to the Quorum of the Twelve Sept. 30, 1978, ordained apostle Oct. 1, 1978, at age 58;
sustained as second counselor to President Gordon B. Hinckley March 12,1995;
died Aug. 10, 2007, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 87.